{"article_id":"t7yk7i217qH3vGbT","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN ) --","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"A little over two days .","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"That 's how long the grand jury deliberated","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"before deciding not to bring an indictment against Darren Wilson , the police officer","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"who shot and killed Michael Brown in Ferguson , Missouri on August 9 .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"St. Louis County Prosecutor Robert McCulloch announced","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"the grand jury had heard more than 70 hours of testimony from 60 witnesses","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"before reaching its decision ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"which","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"he said","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"was supported by physical evidence .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"Sadly , the grand jury 's failure","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"to return an indictment of Wilson","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"was not surprising .","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"But do n't blame the grand jury ;","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"blame McCulloch .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"He oversaw the proceedings","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"and bears responsibility for their outcome .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"McCulloch compromised the Ferguson grand jury proceedings from the start .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"He resisted calls","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"to recuse himself ,","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"saying ,","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"`` I have absolutely no intention","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"of walking away from duties and the responsibilities","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"entrusted in me by the people of this community . ''","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"However , the community would have been better served","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"if he had stepped aside .","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"McCulloch 's father was a police officer","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"killed in a shootout with an African-American suspect .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"His brother , uncle and cousin served with the St. Louis Police Department ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"and his mother worked there for 20 years as a clerk .","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"Newsweek noted McCulloch 's `` long history","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"of siding with the police . ''","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"For the sake of impartiality , McCulloch should have let a special prosecutor take over the case .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"The grand jury only needed to find `` probable cause ''","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"to charge Wilson .","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"That 's one of the lowest legal standards in our justice system , below `` beyond a reasonable doubt ''","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"( required for a criminal conviction )","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"and `` preponderance of the evidence ''","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"( the standard in a civil trial ) .","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"The fact","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"that McCulloch did not get an indictment for a killing","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"that shocked the nation","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"raises questions","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"about whether he really wanted an indictment .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"`` We will be presenting absolutely everything to this grand jury , ''","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"McCulloch said in August .","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"Yet in grand jury proceedings , the prosecutor typically shows the minimal amount of evidence","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"necessary","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"to establish","depth":15},{"id":50,"text":"that a trial is merited .","depth":15},{"id":51,"text":"By dumping so much evidence on the grand jury ,","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"McCulloch may have overwhelmed them","depth":15},{"id":53,"text":"and led them to the wrong conclusion .","depth":15},{"id":54,"text":"In the process , he 's opened himself to charges","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"that he was acting to protect Wilson .","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"Consider McCulloch 's time frame for the grand jury ,","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"which The New York Times described as `` prolonged and exhaustive . ''","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"Grand juries routinely return criminal indictments in a matter of days .","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"But the Ferguson proceedings dragged on for months ,","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"putting a burden on the jurors to recall everything","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"and then decide wisely .","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"Another red flag was that this lengthy process was riddled with leaks ,","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"all of which supported Wilson 's account of the events .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"Worse , McCulloch declined to recommend charges to the grand jury .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"Prosecutors normally walk a jury through the charges","depth":15},{"id":66,"text":"they are seeking ,","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"breaking them down","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"and explaining why they are deserved .","depth":15},{"id":69,"text":"McCulloch instead left the Ferguson grand jury to sort through terms such as `` voluntary manslaughter '' and `` involuntary manslaughter in the second degree '' on their own","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"-- making it more likely that they would not seek an indictment .","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"In fact , McCulloch could have brought charges directly against Wilson ,","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"circumventing the grand jury .","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"He chose not to do so ,","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"which is a troubling indicator of his interest","depth":15},{"id":75,"text":"in aggressively prosecuting this case .","depth":15},{"id":76,"text":"Sure , there are conflicting accounts of what transpired between Wilson and Michael Brown .","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"Was Wilson in fear for his life ,","depth":15},{"id":78,"text":"as he told investigators ,","depth":15},{"id":79,"text":"when he and Brown struggled for his gun ?","depth":14},{"id":80,"text":"Did Brown have his hands up","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"when he was fatally shot ?","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"We will never know ,","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"because there will be no trial .","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"That 's a tragedy for the Brown family","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"and an affront to the fundamental American value","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"that we all are equal under the law .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"The grand jury 's decision has implications far beyond Ferguson .","depth":5},{"id":88,"text":"Gallup polling has found","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"that African-Americans have less confidence in the criminal justice system than white Americans ,","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"while a W.W. Kellogg Foundation report found","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"that 68 % of Latinos report being worried about police brutality .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"Wilson walking free will likely reinforce the views among communities of color","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"that our justice system is unfair .","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"And","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"when significant segments of our population lose faith in our justice system ,","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"our democracy is weakened .","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"The Ferguson decision reflects poorly on prosecutor McCulloch .","depth":4},{"id":98,"text":"His flawed grand jury proceedings ensured","depth":5},{"id":99,"text":"that justice was not served for Michael Brown .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":199,"left":0,"right":198,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":198,"left":185,"right":197,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":185,"left":109,"right":184,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":109,"left":103,"right":108,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":1,"right":102,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":2,"right":101,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"